{
  "title": "Untraditional caring arrangements among parents living apart",
  "abstract": "In spite of quite symmetric parental roles in Norway, shared residence and father sole custody are still rare when parents split up. Several countries have witnessed an increase in shared residence for children recently, and this is also the case in Norway",
